h response was contingent on the post-fire climate. Longleaf pine resin duct size was sensitive to the effects of smoldering fire, and potential negative impacts may be exacerbated by lower precipitation. Restoring fire to long-unburned sites proceeded by warmer and drier climate conditions may result in reduced longleaf pine growth and defense that may contribute to increased probability of mortality during subsequent disturbances.},
